title: Dycom Beats Earnings Estimates
text:
tess.stynes@wsj.com Aug. 25, 2015 5:45 p.m. ET 
Dycom Industries Inc. issued guidance for the current quarter that beat Wall Street estimates and reported better-than-expected earnings and revenue for the three-month period ended in July. 
Shares of the Florida-based provider of contracting services to telecommunications providers and utilities, which already were up 72% this year, rose 9.4%... To Read the Full Story, Subscribe or Sign In Popular on WSJ
